    "result": {"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p><em>In this new post of the series Blender tutorial I will talk about other textures techniques.</em></p>\n<hr>\n<p>In the <a href=\"/2019/03/22/blender-tutorial-8-textures-part-1/\">previous post of the series \"Blender tutorial\"</a> we talked\nabout textures in Blender. In this post we will continue to learn how to use textures in Blender.<br>\nWe will start with normal maps. This kind of texture let us simulate rough surfaces without adding geometric details to\nthe mesh. We can set bump mapping in the texture tab under the Influence section. By checking the Geometry -> Normal\ncheckbox we let the texture be used as a reference to modify the normals of the mesh so that we can simulate additional\ngeometry details. It is possible to modify the quality of the map by adjusting the option in the same panel.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/fccb150f2711fed08305c0f7a549481a/c58a3/blender-normal-mapping.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 63.15789473684211%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Normal mapping\"\n        title=\"Normal mapping\"\n        src=\"/static/fccb150f2711fed08305c0f7a549481a/0470c/blender-normal-mapping.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/fccb150f2711fed08305c0f7a549481a/6c669/blender-normal-mapping.jpg 285w,\n/static/fccb150f2711fed08305c0f7a549481a/882a4/blender-normal-mapping.jpg 570w,\n/static/fccb150f2711fed08305c0f7a549481a/0470c/blender-normal-mapping.jpg 1140w,\n/static/fccb150f2711fed08305c0f7a549481a/c58a3/blender-normal-mapping.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Normal mapping</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>Another interesting texture technique useful to add details to our models is the displacement mapping. Instead of\ncreating the illusion of additional details, the displacement mapping modifies the geometry of an object. We can\nactivate the displacement mapping under the influence section of the texture tab. To obtain better result with the\ndisplacement mapping, it is useful to apply a subdivision surface modifier to the object.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/d6f25e10d48082e90ecf6a656aa7d9bd/c58a3/blender-displacement-mapping.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 63.50877192982456%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Displacement mapping\"\n        title=\"Displacement mapping\"\n        src=\"/static/d6f25e10d48082e90ecf6a656aa7d9bd/0470c/blender-displacement-mapping.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/d6f25e10d48082e90ecf6a656aa7d9bd/6c669/blender-displacement-mapping.jpg 285w,\n/static/d6f25e10d48082e90ecf6a656aa7d9bd/882a4/blender-displacement-mapping.jpg 570w,\n/static/d6f25e10d48082e90ecf6a656aa7d9bd/0470c/blender-displacement-mapping.jpg 1140w,\n/static/d6f25e10d48082e90ecf6a656aa7d9bd/c58a3/blender-displacement-mapping.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Displacement mapping</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>One final tool we have for textures is the node editor. With it we can join multiple textures into a single one to\nobtain a more complex texture. We can activate it in a new window by selecting the \"Node Editor\" visualization. After we\nactivate the \"Use nodes\" option we compose complex texture by adding more node (with the menu at the bottom of the view)\nand we can compose them to obtain our final texture.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/f8f0ff81d3724fdb0a0145304f9053cf/c58a3/blender-node-editor.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 63.50877192982456%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"The node editor\"\n        title=\"The node editor\"\n        src=\"/static/f8f0ff81d3724fdb0a0145304f9053cf/0470c/blender-node-editor.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/f8f0ff81d3724fdb0a0145304f9053cf/6c669/blender-node-editor.jpg 285w,\n/static/f8f0ff81d3724fdb0a0145304f9053cf/882a4/blender-node-editor.jpg 570w,\n/static/f8f0ff81d3724fdb0a0145304f9053cf/0470c/blender-node-editor.jpg 1140w,\n/static/f8f0ff81d3724fdb0a0145304f9053cf/c58a3/blender-node-editor.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">The node editor</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>In the next post we will talk about light.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Blender tutorial: textures - part 2","comments":true,"authors":["fabrizio_duroni"],"tags":["computer graphics","blender"],"date":"23 Mar 2019","description":"In this new post of the series Blender tutorial I will talk other about textures techniques.","math":false,"image":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"fullWidth","backgroundColor":"#383838","images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/d6f25e10d48082e90ecf6a656aa7d9bd/9b75b/blender-displacement-mapping.jpg","srcSet":"/static/d6f25e10d48082e90ecf6a656aa7d9bd/be89c/blender-displacement-mapping.jpg 750w,\n/static/d6f25e10d48082e90ecf6a656aa7d9bd/204bd/blender-displacement-mapping.jpg 1080w,\n/static/d6f25e10d48082e90ecf6a656aa7d9bd/5b183/blender-displacement-mapping.jpg 1366w,\n/static/d6f25e10d48082e90ecf6a656aa7d9bd/9b75b/blender-displacement-mapping.jpg 1500w","sizes":"100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/static/d6f25e10d48082e90ecf6a656aa7d9bd/53bd5/blender-displacement-mapping.webp 750w,\n/static/d6f25e10d48082e90ecf6a656aa7d9bd/e941d/blender-displacement-mapping.webp 1080w,\n/static/d6f25e10d48082e90ecf6a656aa7d9bd/de9f7/blender-displacement-mapping.webp 1366w,\n/static/d6f25e10d48082e90ecf6a656aa7d9bd/0da6f/blender-displacement-mapping.webp 1500w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"100vw"}]},"width":1,"height":0.6333333333333333}}}},"fields":{"slug":"/2019/03/23/blender-tutor